### SIMPLE JOB WORKFLOW TEST

### 1. LOGIN AS EMPLOYER

post http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "employer@test.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### 2. CREATE JOB (Employer)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_EMPLOYER_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "React Developer",
  "company": "Tech Corp",
  "location": "Remote",
  "type": "Full-time",
  "salaryMin": 800000,
  "salaryMax": 1200000,
  "description": "Looking for React developer",
  "requirements": "React, JavaScript",
  "skills": "React,JavaScript,HTML,CSS",
  "deadline": "2026-12-31"
}

### 3. LOGIN AS COLLEGE
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "college@test.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### 4. APPROVE JOB (College - use JOB_ID from step 2)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/JOB_ID_HERE/status
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_COLLEGE_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "approved"
}

### 5. LOGIN AS STUDENT
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student@test.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### 6. SEE APPROVED JOBS (Student)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/approved
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_STUDENT_TOKEN